Fig. 4 illustrates that roller boundary conditions are applied to the top, right, and bottom boundaries. As noted in the introduction, external pressure can be applied to ASSB structure to reduce fracture and phase separation, ensuring solid–solid interface contact is maintained. Pressure effects are investigated in subsequent sections. The present model assumes the structure to be stress-free at the initial condition (
x = 0 . 97
). This assumption neglects the effect of residual stress developed during the fabrication process. These residual stress effects are the focus of ongoing studies.
